                           <q xml:lang="en"> Fol. 233rb: This is the book of Täklä Haymanot who acquired it with his own money. The one who stole (what is written in) it or the one who scratched it without the permission of the abbot shall be excomunicated by the authority of Peter and Paul.</q>
                           The note is written in the same hand as the one that added the name of the donor Täklä Haymanot.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#233va">Fols. 233va-234</locus>rb: Excerpt from ʾArganonä wǝddase “The Harp of Praise”.<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Written in a different, less regular and skilled hand. Cp. the main text fols. 233va-234rb (the list of the saints mentioned is somewhat different from the standard version).
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The title of Text II is crudely written on the back board with yellow paint.&#xD;
- The last two lines on fol. 161vb are written in a different hand. &#xD;
